- Are there security concerns?
- Are trust boundaries violated?
- Are there injection vulnerabilities when parsing untrusted inputs?
- Are secrets and other sensitive data properly stored, tightly access-controlled and protected in transit?
- Is error handling hardened to prevent leakage of sensitive information?
- Is authentication using secure credentials, strong session management and brute force protection?
- Is authorization enforced at every endpoint and object, making sure users can only access explicitly granted resources and actions?
- Are swallowed or mismatched errors prevented from granting access or hiding security failures?
- Are security related edge cases handled?
- Are security controls implemented without harming code readability or maintainability or introducing unnecessary complexity?
